{"description":"Such code : \n\n{code}\nObserver observer \u003d (o, arg) -\u003e {\n            if (arg !\u003d null) {\n                System.out.println(arg);\n            }\n        };\n\nObserver observer \u003d (o, arg) -\u003e {\n            try {\n                String test \u003d (String) arg;\n                ...\n            }\n            catch (ClassCastException e) {\n            }\n        };\n{code}\nshould not raise issue as, even if there is one statement in lambda body, it contains more than one instruction (and it is not a valid lambda construction).\nSource : http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24364298/sonar-lambda-remove-useless-curly-braces-around-statement","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"2.4"}